headline: eBay price target raised to $63 from $59 at BMO Capital
summary: BMO Capital analyst Brian Pitz raised the firm’s price target on eBay (EBAY) to $63 from $59 and keeps a Market Perform rating on the shares after its Q4 earnings beat. The company is executing well, with Focus Categories growth accelerating to 6% and Trading Cards and P&A showing notable strength, the analyst tells investors in a research note. BMO stays at neutral however given the uncertain tariff outlook and Q1 GMV – Gross Merchandise Volume – guidance. Published first on TheFly – the ultima
